00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:32.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see. I’m hoping for a positive reply.

284
00:16:32.491 --> 00:16:33.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
TAXI STOP

285
00:16:33.742 --> 00:16:37.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yasu, I’m gonna take a taxi
with Nobu and Shin.

286
00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:41.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hachiko said she’s working
from the morning tomorrow,

287
00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:42.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so I’ll drop by to see her tonight.

288
00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:45.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, that would be good.

289
00:16:45.212 --> 00:16:46.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Send her my apologies
for not being able to make it

290
00:16:46.839 --> 00:16:48.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to the after-party.

291
00:16:51.343 --> 00:16:55.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Kawano is such
a laid-back type of man, don’t you think?

292
00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:58.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At this rate, it’s gonna take us
one hundred years before our debut.

293
00:16:58.392 --> 00:17:01.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does a man like that really understand
the likes of rock and punk?

294
00:17:02.271 --> 00:17:05.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure, he said that he was moved, but…

295
00:17:07.192 --> 00:17:09.945 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Still, he gave us money for the cab,
so I’m sure he’s a good man.

296
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:14.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m not sure if that determines
whether or not he’s a good man.

297
00:17:14.116 --> 00:17:16.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let’s split the change.

298
00:17:16.952 --> 00:17:18.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me! Stop here!

299
00:17:21.832 --> 00:17:22.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it?

300
00:17:22.958 --> 00:17:26.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Work? Where do you get all that energy?

301
00:17:26.170 --> 00:17:28.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say hi to Hachi for me, Nobu.

302
00:17:32.718 --> 00:17:35.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you planning on coming too?
-I’m not.

303
00:17:35.971 --> 00:17:38.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I give up. There are lots
of women out there.

304
00:17:39.016 --> 00:17:40.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I’m pretty popular with the girls.

305
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At least grow your hair, Nobuo.

306
00:17:42.811 --> 00:17:45.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll get no pleasure winning
her over in that department!

307
00:17:45.355 --> 00:17:46.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, I don’t think
it’ll look good on you.

308
00:17:46.857 --> 00:17:48.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then don’t say it!

309
00:17:51.570 --> 00:17:52.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m back.

310
00:17:55.324 --> 00:17:56.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry for waking you.

311
00:17:56.617 --> 00:17:59.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I forgot my key at my friend’s place.

312
00:17:59.369 --> 00:18:00.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
REN'S PLACE?

313
00:18:00.287 --> 00:18:02.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it's fine. I was still awake.

314
00:18:02.498 --> 00:18:03.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about Hachi? Has she gone to bed?

315
00:18:03.957 --> 00:18:05.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah…

316
00:18:06.335 --> 00:18:08.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Hachiko went out a short while ago.

317
00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:11.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Huh? Where could she have gone
at this hour?

318
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:14.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m not sure,
but she suddenly left in a flurry,

319
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:17.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
saying she wouldn’t be returning tonight.

320
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:24.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I might’ve done something
to upset her again.

321
00:18:24.311 --> 00:18:26.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it’s not that. I’m sure it’s a guy.

322
00:18:27.106 --> 00:18:28.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll bet she went to see her boyfriend.

323
00:18:29.066 --> 00:18:30.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Don’t worry.
-Huh?

324
00:18:30.651 --> 00:18:32.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Is the beer cold?
-Yes.

325
00:18:33.779 --> 00:18:36.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So Ms. Hachiko has a boyfriend?

326
00:18:37.783 --> 00:18:39.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why? Does it surprise you?

327
00:18:39.201 --> 00:18:40.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes!

328
00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:41.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Yes," she says.

329
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:45.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because to me, it seemed that
Ms. Hachiko thinks only of you, Nana.

330
00:18:47.292 --> 00:18:48.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There’s no way.

331
00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:51.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I think only of you, Nana.

332
00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:54.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Making remarks like that as
if it were impossible hurts my feelings.

333
00:18:55.843 --> 00:18:58.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry.

334
00:18:59.596 --> 00:19:01.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s this?

335
00:19:01.181 --> 00:19:02.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, it’s a microwave.

336
00:19:02.683 --> 00:19:04.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I can tell that
by looking at it, but…

337
00:19:04.518 --> 00:19:06.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She said she got a loan to buy it.

338
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:08.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Apparently, that was the only place
she could put it.

339
00:19:09.064 --> 00:19:11.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If she had that kind of money,
why not get an air conditioner?

340
00:19:11.775 --> 00:19:14.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Geez, that Hachi.

341
00:19:25.289 --> 00:19:29.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Say, what’s with this mountain
of leftovers in the fridge?

342
00:19:30.043 --> 00:19:35.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That… Actually, Ms. Hachiko figured
tonight would be a night to celebrate,

343
00:19:35.924 --> 00:19:39.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and she had already prepared this
before I arrived here.

344
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:42.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Did you already make preparations</i>
<i>for our after-party?</i>

345
00:19:42.264 --> 00:19:45.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No, not yet. Don’t worry about us and go.</i>

346
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:51.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry.

347
00:19:51.732 --> 00:19:54.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, you couldn’t help it, Nana.

348
00:19:54.818 --> 00:19:57.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, so how did it go
with the record company?

349
00:20:16.256 --> 00:20:17.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hey, Nana…</i>

350
00:20:19.176 --> 00:20:21.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>For instance, if we were lovers,</i>

351
00:20:21.929 --> 00:20:26.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>would we have been able to fill</i>
<i>the gap between us with a hug?</i>

352
00:20:31.271 --> 00:20:37.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Or… does everyone endure this loneliness?</i>

353
00:20:57.506 --> 00:21:00.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It’s not that I wanted</i>
<i>to keep you all to myself, Nana.</i>

354
00:21:01.927 --> 00:21:04.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I just wanted to be needed by you.</i>

